Huh? what? Do a little more research dude...most mid size SUV with 7+ 
passengers and a V6 engine are running on 240-290hp so 270 is pretty inline 
with the competition; same to the fuel economy. If you looking for fuel 
economy with power then you can pick those I4 with turbo, however, they 
cannot tow as much as a V6. Only one that stands out is Ford's EcoBoost V6 
similar fuel economy with much more power. Then again you will need to fill 
it with 93 octane and above so I don't know how much you save. Honestly a 
family hauler with all your kids and loved ones in it do not need to be 
super quick. 0-60 in about 7-8 seconds, strong crash test rating and decent 
towing is where the market is. Slow down, drive defensively and safely, and 
protect your loved ones.﻿
